        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="2384.621" end="x">Now tell me . . . what happened to him?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Dimitri Odinets</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="odinetsD" start="2390.339" end="x">His fate is not clear to me. I know only that at the time of the liberation of <a class="placename" href="#vothL13">Paris</a> from the Germans he was in the possession of large sums of money and walked openly through the streets of <a class="placename" href="#vothL13">Paris</a>. However, the authorities of liberation caught up with him and for a time he was arrested. His further fate is not known to me, but rumors have it that he was released.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="2437.077" end="x">Now tell me in general . . . give us a general picture to the extent to which you were able to observe, or read . . . in your capacity of the editor of a newspaper . . . First of all, the "Soviet Patriot" has emerged from the underground?</span>
